\begin{align*}
x + y &= 30 \\
0.2x + 0.3y &= \text{total points}
\end{align*}
We want to find the value of $3(0.2x) + 2(0.3y)$, which is the total points Shenille scored. First, we solve for $x$ in the first equation: $x = 30 - y$. Then, substitute this into the second equation:
\begin{align*}
0.2(30 - y) + 0.3y &= \text{total points} \\
6 - 0.2y + 0.3y &= \text{total points} \\
6 + 0.1y &= \text{total points}
\end{align*}
Now, substitute $y = 30 - x$ back into the equation for total points:
\begin{align*}
6 + 0.1(30 - x) &= \text{total points} \\
6 + 3 - 0.1x &= \text{total points} \\
9 - 0.1x &= \text{total points}
\end{align*}
Finally, substitute this expression for total points into the expression we want to find the value of:
\begin{align*}
3(0.2x) + 2(0.3y) &= 3(0.2x) + 2(0.3(30 - x)) \\
&= 0.6x + 18 - 0.6x \\
&= 18
\end{align*}
So, Shenille scored $\boxed{18}$ points.

